import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.PrintWriter;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
class CountPalindromes {
	public static void main(String arg[])throws Exception{
		BufferedReader br=new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));
		PrintWriter pr=new PrintWriter(System.out,true);

	int q,i,k,h1,h2,m1,m2,s1,s2,l,h,c;
	
	String s[],sb[];
	q=Integer.parseInt(br.readLine());
	while(q-->0){
		sb=br.readLine().split(" ");
		s=sb[0].split(":");
		h1=Integer.parseInt(s[0]);
		m1=Integer.parseInt(s[1]);
		s1=Integer.parseInt(s[2]);
		s=sb[1].split(":");
		h2=Integer.parseInt(s[0]);
		m2=Integer.parseInt(s[1]);
		s2=Integer.parseInt(s[2]);
		c=0;
		
		if(h1==h2){
			if((h1>5&&h1<10||h1>15&&h1<20));
				
			else{
				l=h1%10;h=h1/10;k=l*10+h;
				if(s1>k)
					m1++;
				
				if(s2<k)
					m2--;
				
				if(m1%11!=0)
					m1=m1-m1%11+11;
				for(i=m1;i<=m2;i+=11){
					c++;
				}
			}
			h1=8;
			h2=7;
		}
		for(i=h1+1;i<h2;i++){
			if(i>5&&i<10){
				i=9;continue;
			}
			if(i>15&&i<20){
				i=19;continue;
			}
			c+=6;
		}
		if(!(h1>5&&h1<10||h1>15&&h1<20)){
			l=h1%10;h=h1/10;k=l*10+h;
			if(s1>k)
				m1++;
			
			if(m1%11!=0)
				m1=m1-m1%11+11;
			while(m1<=55){
				c++;
				m1+=11;
			}
		}
		if(!(h2>5&&h2<10||h2>15&&h2<20)){
			i=0;
			l=h2%10;h=h2/10;k=l*10+h;
			if(s2<k)
				m2--;
			while(i<=m2){
				c++;
				i+=11;
			}
		}
		
		pr.println(c);	
	}
	
	
	
	
	}}
